HARDWARE

CPU info: /proc/cpuinfo
RAM info: free (command) show RAM status
	  free -m(megabytes) -g(gigabytes)
MoBoard info: dmidecode (command) Mobo info, processor, ramtype, bios
POWERSuppliers
HD: /dev (contain info as device)
    names for disk will be "/dev/sda" /dev/sdb" and so goes one
Partitions also, are named as "sdaX" like "/dev/sda1"
Commands:
lsblk : see all the hard drives in system
df: to see space 
    -h: human readable information flag
OPTICAL DRIVES.
